<inglise> Council Regulation (EEC) No 1883/78 of 2 August 1978 laying down general rules for the financing of interventions by the European Agricultural Guidance and Guarantee Fund, Guarantee Section </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 1883/78, millega kehtestatakse &uuml;ldeeskirjad sekkumise finantseerimiseks P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfondi tagatisrahastust 2. august 1978 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 729/70 of 21 April 1970 on the financing of the common agricultural policy (1), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 2788/72 (2), and in particular Article 3 (2) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 21. aprilli 1970. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 &uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika rahastamise kohta (1) (viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 2788/72), (2) eriti selle artikli 3 l&otilde;iget 2, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in accordance with Article 3 (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 729/70, the general rules for the Community financing of interventions should be laid down; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 artikli 3 l&otilde;ikele 2 tuleks kehtestada &uuml;ldeeskirjad sekkumise rahastamiseks &uuml;henduse poolt; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, to this end, the list of measures complying with the concept of intervention intended to stabilize the markets should be drawn up; </inglise>
<eesti> selleks tuleks koostada loetelu meetmetest, mis vastavad turu stabiliseerimiseks m&otilde;eldud sekkumise p&otilde;him&otilde;ttele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is desirable to lay down that expenditure resulting from intervention measures for which a sum per unit is determined within the framework of a common organization of markets shall be met entirely from Community funds; </inglise>
<eesti> on soovitav s&auml;testada, et seoses selliste sekkumismeetmetega tekkivaid kulutusi, millele on &uuml;hise turukorralduse raames ette n&auml;htud kindel summa &uuml;hiku kohta, rahastatakse t&auml;ielikult &uuml;henduse vahenditest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas in the case of intervention measures in respect of which a sum per unit is not determined within the framework of the common organization of markets, basic rules should be laid down with regard in particular to the method for determining the amounts to be financed, the financing of expenditure resulting from the tying-up of the funds necessary for intervention purchasing of products, the valuation of stocks to be carried forward from one financial year to the next and the financing of expenditure resulting from storage and, where appropriate, processing operations; </inglise>
<eesti> kui tegemist on sekkumismeetmetega, mille puhul ei ole &uuml;hise turukorralduse raames kindlat summat &uuml;hiku kohta ette n&auml;htud, tuleks s&auml;testada p&otilde;hieeskirjad, milles k&auml;sitletakse eelk&otilde;ige rahastatavate summade m&auml;&auml;ramise meetodit, toodete sekkumisostudeks vajalike rahaliste vahendite sidumisest tekkivate kulutuste rahastamist, &uuml;hest eelarveaastast j&auml;rgmisse &uuml;lekantavate varude maksumuse m&auml;&auml;ramist ning ladustamisest ja vajaduse korral t&ouml;&ouml;tlemistoimingutest tulenevate kulude rahastamist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the various items of expenditure and revenue to be adopted for each sector on the basis of these rules should be the subject of more detailed regulations; where the financing regulations for each sector should, in the meantime, be maintained in force; </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealuste eeskirjade alusel igas sektoris etten&auml;htud eri tulu- ja kuluartikleid tuleks reguleerida &uuml;ksikasjalikumate eeskirjadega; samal ajal peaksid rahastamist k&auml;sitlevad m&auml;&auml;rused igas sektoris edasi kehtima; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the general rules for Community financing of interventions should be embodied in a single Regulation; whereas Council Regulation (EEC) No 2824/72 of 28 December 1972 laying down general rules for the financing of interventions by the Guarantee Section of the European Agricultural Guidance and Guarantee Fund (4) should be repealed, </inglise>
<eesti> &uuml;ldeeskirjad sekkumise rahastamiseks &uuml;henduse poolt peaksid sisalduma &uuml;hes m&auml;&auml;ruses; n&otilde;ukogu 28. detsembri 1972. aasta m&auml;&auml;rus (EM&Uuml;) nr 2824/72 (millega kehtestatakse &uuml;ldeeskirjad sekkumise finantseerimiseks P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfondi tagatisrahastust) (4) tuleks kehtetuks tunnistada, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The measures listed in the Annex shall comply with the concept of intervention intended to stabilize the agricultural markets within the meaning of Article 3 (1) of Regulation (EEC) No 729/70. </inglise>
<eesti> Lisas loetletud meetmed vastavad (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 artikli 3 l&otilde;ikes 1 kohaselt p&otilde;llumajandusturgude tasakaalustamiseks m&otilde;eldud sekkumise p&otilde;him&otilde;ttele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Where, within the framework of a common organization of the market, a sum per unit is determined for an intervention measure, the resulting expenditure shall be met entirely by Community funds. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui &uuml;hise turukorralduse raames on sekkumismeetme puhul m&auml;&auml;ratud kindel summa &uuml;hiku kohta, finantseeritakse sellest tulenevad kulud t&auml;ielikult &uuml;henduse rahalistest vahenditest. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Where, within the framework of a common organization of the market, a sum per unit is not determined in respect of an intervention measure, the measure concerned shall be financed by the EAGGF, Guarantee Section, in accordance with the provisions contained in Articles 4 to 8. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui &uuml;hise turukorralduse raames ei ole sekkumismeetme puhul m&auml;&auml;ratud kindlat summat &uuml;hiku kohta, siis finantseerib k&otilde;nealust meedet Euroopa P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfondi tagatisrahastu vastavalt artiklite 4-8 s&auml;tetele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Where an intervention measure referred to in Article 3 involves the buying-in and storage of products, the amount financed shall be determined by the annual accounts drawn up by the payment services or agencies, in which the various items of expenditure and revenue have been respectively debited and credited. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui artiklis 3 osutatud sekkumismeede h&otilde;lmab toodete kokkuostu ja ladustamist, m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahastatav summa kindlaks maksetalituste v&otilde;i makseasutuse koostatud aastaaruannete p&otilde;hjal, milles eri tulu- ja kuluartiklid on vastavalt kas debiteeritud v&otilde;i krediteeritud. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The financing of the other intervention measures referred to in Article 3 shall be equal to the expediture, less any revenue, resulting from the intervention measure. </inglise>
<eesti> Muid artiklis 3 osutatud sekkumismeetmeid rahastatakse v&otilde;rdses ulatuses kuludega, millest lahutatakse k&otilde;ik v&otilde;imalikud sekkumismeetmetest tulenevad tulud. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The Council, acting by a qualified majority on a proposal from the Commission, shall in respect of the intervention measures referred to in paragraph 1, lay down the rules and conditions governing the annual accounts and, where necessary in respect of the intervention measures referred to in paragraph 2, determine the items to be taken into account for purposes of financing where these have not been determined within the framework of a common organization of the market. </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu kehtestab komisjoni ettepanekul kvalifitseeritud h&auml;&auml;lteenamusega l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud sekkumismeetmete suhtes aastaaruandeid reguleerivad eeskirjad ja tingimused ning vajaduse korral m&auml;&auml;rab l&otilde;ikes 2 osutatud sekkumismeetmete puhul kindlaks rahastamisel arvesse v&otilde;etavad artiklid, kui need ei ole &uuml;hise turukorralduse raames kindlaks m&auml;&auml;ratud. </eesti>
<inglise> Until these matters are determined, and save any provision to the contrary of this Regulation, Regulations (EEC) No 786/69 (1), (EEC) No 787/69 (2), (EEC) No 788/69 (3), (EEC) No 2334/69 (4), (EEC) No 2305/70 (5), (EEC) No 2306/70 (6), (EEC) No 1697/71 (7), (EEC) No 272/72 (8) and (EEC) No 273/72 (9) relating to the financing of intervention expenditure in the various sectors shall remain in force. </inglise>
<eesti> Kuni nimetatud tegurite kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramiseni ning kui k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses ei s&auml;testata teisiti, j&auml;&auml;vad kehtima eri sektorites sekkumiskulude rahastamist k&auml;sitlevad j&auml;rgmised m&auml;&auml;rused: (EM&Uuml;) nr 786/69, (5) (EM&Uuml;) nr 787/69, (6) (EM&Uuml;) nr 788/69, (7) (EM&Uuml;) nr 2334/69, (8) (EM&Uuml;) nr 2305/70, (9) (EM&Uuml;) nr 2306/70, (10) (EM&Uuml;) nr 1697/71, (11) (EM&Uuml;) nr 272/72 (12) ja (EM&Uuml;) nr 273/72. (13) </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> In the case of funds originating in the Member States used for intervention purchasing of products, the amount of the interest charges to be financed by the EAGGF, Guarantee Section, shall be calculated using a method and an interest rate uniform throughout the Community, to be determined in accordance with the procedure laid down in accordance with Article 13 of Regulation (EEC) No 729/70. </inglise>
<eesti> Nende liikmesriikidest p&auml;rinevate rahaliste vahendite puhul, mida kasutatakse toodete sekkumisostudeks, arvutatakse P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfondi tagatisrahastust finantseeritav intressikulu summa kogu &uuml;henduses sama meetodi ja intressim&auml;&auml;ra p&otilde;hjal, mis m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 artiklis 13 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise> The interest rate must be representative of the interest rates actually paid. </inglise>
<eesti> Intressim&auml;&auml;r peab vastama tegelikult makstavatele intressim&auml;&auml;radele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> Material operations arising from the storage and, where appropriate, processing of intervention products shall be financed by the EAGGF, Guarantee Section, by means of standard amounts uniform throughout the Community, to be laid down in accordance with the procedure provided for in Article 13 of Regulation (EEC) No 729/70 and, where necessary, after examination of the matter by the management committee concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> Sekkumistoodete ladustamisest ja vajaduse korral t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisest tulenevaid materiaalseid toiminguid finantseeritakse Euroopa P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfondi tagatisrahastust kogu &uuml;henduses &uuml;htsete standardsummadena, mis kehtestatakse m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 artiklis 13 s&auml;testatud korras ning vajaduse korral p&auml;rast seda, kui k&uuml;simust on uurinud asjaomane korralduskomitee. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> Where the products in question have experienced a depreciation as a result of storage, the financial effect thereof shall be recorded and taken into account at the time of entry into intervention. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui k&otilde;nealuste toodete tarbimisv&auml;&auml;rtus on ladustamise tagaj&auml;rjel langenud, registreeritakse tarbimisv&auml;&auml;rtuse languse rahaline m&otilde;ju ja seda arvestatakse sekkumist alustades. </eesti>
<inglise> To that end, the coefficients of depreciation and the prices to which they apply shall be determined in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 26 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 2727/75 of 29 October 1975 on the common organization of the market in cereals (10), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 1254/78 (11), or, as the case may be, in the corresponding Article in the other Regulations on the common organization of agricultural markets, and where necessary, after examination by the EAGGF Committee. </inglise>
<eesti> Sel eesm&auml;rgil m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks tarbimisv&auml;&auml;rtuse v&auml;henemise koefitsient ja hinnad, mille suhtes seda kohaldatakse, teraviljaturu &uuml;hist korraldust k&auml;sitleva n&otilde;ukogu 29. oktoobri 1975. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2727/75 (14) (viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1254/78) (15) artiklis 26 s&auml;testatud korras v&otilde;i vastavalt olukorrale muude p&otilde;llumajandustoodete turu &uuml;hist korraldust k&auml;sitlevate m&auml;&auml;ruste vastavates artiklites, vajaduse korral p&auml;rast seda, kui k&uuml;simust on uurinud Euroopa P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfondi komitee. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> In the annual accounts referred to in Article 4 (1), the quantities of products in storage to be carried forward to the following financial year shall, as a rule, be valued at their purchase price. </inglise>
<eesti> Artikli 4 l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud aastaaruannetes m&auml;&auml;ratakse &uuml;hest eelarveaastast j&auml;rgmisse &uuml;lekantavate varude maksumus &uuml;ldjuhul vastavalt nende ostuhinnale. </eesti>
<inglise> To this end, on the basis of the purchase prices paid by the intervention agencies over a reference period and taking into account the depreciation referred to in Article 7, the price to be applied for quantities to be carried forward to the following financial year shall be determined for the various products in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 13 of Regulation (EEC) No 729/70. </inglise>
<eesti> Selleks m&auml;&auml;ratakse eri toodete j&auml;rgmisse eelarveaastasse &uuml;lekantavate koguste suhtes kohaldatav hind m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 artiklis 13 s&auml;testatud korras, l&auml;htudes ostuhinnast, mida sekkumisametid v&otilde;rdlusperioodi jooksul on maksnud, ja v&otilde;ttes arvesse artiklis 7 nimetatud tarbimisv&auml;&auml;rtuse langust. </eesti>
<inglise> However, if, for a given product, the estimated price on leaving intervention is substantially lower than the value of stocks to be carried forward as determined in accordance with the first subparagraph, a decision may be taken to replace the purchase prices paid by the intervention agencies by another price. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui teatava toote eeldatav hind on sekkumise l&otilde;ppedes oluliselt madalam kui &uuml;lekantavate varude esimese l&otilde;igu kohaselt m&auml;&auml;ratud v&auml;&auml;rtus, v&otilde;ib siiski teha otsuse asendada sekkumisametite makstud ostuhind muu hinnaga. </eesti>
<inglise> The latter price shall be fixed in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 13 of Regulation (EEC) No 729/70, and if necessary after examination by the management committee concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> Uus hind m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 artiklis 13 s&auml;testatud korras ning vajaduse korral p&auml;rast seda, kui k&uuml;simust on uurinud asjaomane korralduskomitee. </eesti>
<inglise> It may not be below the average of the purchase prices and the prices obtained on disposal of intervention stocks. </inglise>
<eesti> See ei v&otilde;i olla madalam kui ostuhindade keskmine ja sekkumisvarude realiseerimisel saadud hind. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 9 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 9 </eesti>
<inglise> Where necessary, detailed implementing rules of this Regulation shall be adopted in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 13 Regulation (EEC) No 729/70. </inglise>
<eesti> Vajaduse korral v&otilde;etakse k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse &uuml;ksikasjalikud rakenduseeskirjad vastu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 artiklis 13 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 10 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 10 </eesti>
<inglise> Regulation (EEC) No 2824/72 is hereby repealed. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevaga tunnistatakse m&auml;&auml;rus (EM&Uuml;) nr 2824/72 kehtetuks. </eesti>
 